A dog had to plucked to safety by rescuers after it fell through ice on a pond and could not escape.

Firefighters rescued the Springer Spaniel called Milo after it plunged through ice on a pond at Eastwood Farm nature reserve in Broomhill, Bristol, and was unable to get to safety.

The owner of Milo, aged two and a half, called 999 after he fell into the water during a walk.

