He slipped through the ice and was in the water for around 25 minutes before he managed to climb up onto an island in the middle of the pond.

When firefighters arrived they used an inflatable walkway to reach the island, and two members of the crew walked across to Milo.

They were then able to get a lead onto the dog and walked him back to safety, where he was reunited with his owner. He was cold and wet, but otherwise unhurt.

