A spokesman for Avon Fire & Rescue Service said she wanted to remind people to take when outside during the cold weather.

She added: ‘Never venture onto frozen water. It may look solid but can break easily and anyone falling in will quickly feel the effects which could lead to hypothermia or worse.

‘Always dial 999 and ask for the fire and rescue service. We have the equipment and training to deal with incidents of this nature.’

